      "term": "allomones",
      "kind": "word",
      "cefrLevel": "C1",
      "senses": [
        {
          "pos": "noun",
          "definition": "Chemical substances released by one species that change the behavior or body of another species in a way that helps the sender but not the receiver.",
          "examples": [
            "Many plants produce allomones to deter insect herbivores from feeding on their leaves.",[1][2][3][4]
            "The wasp uses powerful allomones to confuse its predators during an attack."[2][3][4][1]
          ],
          "collocations": [
            "produce allomones",
